1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
Fast general defenses versus slower targeted memory — your immune system uses both.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:09,200
Innate immunity acts like a first responder, attacking invaders immediately.

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:12,400
But did you know it has no memory?

4
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:15,600
Enter adaptive immunity, which learns and remembers threats.

5
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:18,400
It’s slower but packs a powerful punch.

6
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:24,400
Studies show that the memory cells from adaptive immunity can last years, ready for action.

7
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:29,600
Together, they form a dynamic duo, ensuring your body fights off infections efficiently.

8
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:32,800
Want to learn more about your immune system?

9
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:34,400
Hit that follow button!
